<br />

<br />
How pathetic is it that we're the only class that can get excited by one more point of mana regen per tick?
<br />

<br />
Last night, Code of Silence took a shot at the VP key dragon in Skyfire.  We were very shorthanded and had no idea what we were doing -- like forgetting Kunark dragons require melee range for casting -- but we still got him to 6% on the first try.  We were doing CR and my roommate's druid, who has a 5K+ mana pool, was medding in front of me.  Since we can see our exact mana numbers now, I asked him how much mana he was generating per tick.  He had C5, Bot9, roughly FT15, MC1 AA, and Chorus of Marr from me (lvl 65 and JF3).  He was getting 84 mana per tick.  I checked my own regen.  I was getting 14.  15 if I sat down.
<br />

<br />
Took him fifteen minutes to stop laughing.  That's how long it took me to generate enough mana for two fades.  Sad.  Just sad.</span></td>
