				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bardic Mana?<a name="56990"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 16 04 5:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree, mana regen is fine the way it is now. If you max out your FT and MC you can get 22 standing/23 sitting which is just over/under four minutes a fade. With VoQ I can do six fades and I know higher end bards that can do more. This gives me the play room. If I need to fade a few times on one pull, I still have the cushion to keep pulling. If the raid wipes, I can get enough mana for a couple of fades during the the CR buffing phase, because I'm targeted for an early rezz. If I die pulling, I try for a divine rezz or someone else has to take over for awhile. Or we wait. Which has actually happened, the entire raid waited for me to regen mana for a fade. Which has made getting that divine rezz much easier.
<br />

<br />
But I don't consider FM to be only a &quot;get out of jail free card.&quot; Its a valuable pulling tool, just like feign death is for monks. When you can't pacify, when you can't mezz, whatcha ya gonna do to split those mobs? But you don't need it constantly, because not every pull needs a split. Once you've broken an area, it becomes easer and there is time to regen. It works well as it is. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
